head: sweet potato sheet cake
tail: preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (180 degrees C) and spray a 9x13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray

head: sweet potato sheet cake
tail: whisk together a yellow cake mix, mashed sweet potatoes, eggs, milk, and oil

head: sweet potato sheet cake
tail: stir in chopped nuts and spread the batter evenly into the prepared pan

head: sweet potato sheet cake
tail: bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean

head: sweet potato sheet cake
tail: let the cake cool on a wire rack

head: sweet potato sheet cake
tail: in another bowl, beat softened Neufchâtel cheese, softened butter, and vanilla extract together

head: sweet potato sheet cake
tail: add powdered sugar and beat until well combined

head: sweet potato sheet cake
tail: spread the frosting evenly over the cooled cake and sprinkle with chopped nuts
